## RTL-052d Fix Applied — Port-127 Bug (2026-03-09)

### Root Cause

`C:\Users\PLUTO\github\openclaw\.env` (baked into the Docker image as `/app/.env` via `COPY . .`) contained `OPENCLAW_GATEWAY_PORT=127.0.0.1:18789` — Docker Compose port-mapping syntax, not a plain port number. OpenClaw's `loadDotEnv()` injects this into `process.env` at runtime. `resolveGatewayPort()` calls `parseInt("127.0.0.1:18789", 10)` which stops at the first dot and returns **127**. This caused `openclaw dashboard` to generate `http://127.0.0.1:127/` instead of `:18789`.

Secondary issue: same `.env` contained stale `OPENCLAW_GATEWAY_TOKEN=rSGE...lig=` (old base64 token). Masked at runtime by the higher-precedence Docker Compose `environment:` block, but a latent risk.

### Changes Applied (Option A)

**File:** `C:\Users\PLUTO\github\openclaw\.env`
**Backup:** `C:\Users\PLUTO\github\openclaw\.env.bak`

| Line | Before | After |
|------|--------|-------|
| 13 | `OPENCLAW_GATEWAY_PORT=127.0.0.1:18789` | `OPENCLAW_GATEWAY_PORT=18789` |
| 20 | `OPENCLAW_GATEWAY_TOKEN=rSGE...lig=` | `OPENCLAW_GATEWAY_TOKEN=5722...5461` (active token) |

### Rebuild / Recreate

- `docker compose down` — stopped and removed both containers + network
- `docker build -t openclaw:local .` — rebuilt image with fixed `.env` baked at `/app/.env`
- `docker compose up -d` — recreated containers from new image

Note: `docker compose build` returned "No services to build" because `docker-compose.yml` uses `image: openclaw:local` (pre-built), not a `build:` directive. Direct `docker build` was required.

### Validation Results

| Check | Result |
|-------|--------|
| Backup created | `.env.bak` at `C:\Users\PLUTO\github\openclaw\.env.bak` |
| Container status | `openclaw-openclaw-gateway-1` — Up, healthy |
| `/app/.env` inside container — PORT | `OPENCLAW_GATEWAY_PORT=18789` |
| `/app/.env` inside container — TOKEN | Active token (matches runtime env) |
| `parseInt("18789", 10)` | **18789** (correct) |
| `openclaw dashboard --no-open` URL | `http://127.0.0.1:18789/#token=...` — port **18789** |

### OBSTACLES LOG

| # | Obstacle | Resolution | Impact |
|---|----------|------------|--------|
| 1 | `docker compose build` returned "No services to build" — compose uses pre-built `openclaw:local` image, not a `build:` directive | Used `docker build -t openclaw:local .` directly to rebuild the image | None — image rebuilt successfully, compose picked it up on `up -d` |

