## RTL-047 Phase 2 — ToolApprovalCard UI (2026-03-10)

**Goal:** Render inline approval cards in the message stream when `exec.approval.requested` fires with `decision === 'ask'`.

**Files created:**
- `src/components/chat/ToolApprovalCard.tsx` — New component: ShieldAlert icon, command display, category badge, countdown timer (1s interval), 3 action buttons (Allow Once / Allow Always / Deny), locked state after resolution/expiry

**Files modified:**
- `src/components/chat/ClawdChatInterface.tsx`:
  - Import: `ToolApprovalCard`, `ApprovalDecision`
  - State: `pendingApprovals` (Map<string, ApprovalRecord>) — reactive state for UI rendering
  - `exec.approval.requested` handler: populates `pendingApprovals` when decision is 'ask'
  - `exec.approval.resolved` handler: updates `pendingApprovals` for user-facing cards
  - Timeout handler: updates `pendingApprovals` on expiry
  - New `handleApprovalDecision` callback: sends `exec.approval.resolve` RPC via `sendRef.current()`, updates all state
  - `handleNewConversation`: clears approval timers + state
  - JSX: Renders approval cards after messages in scrollable container
- `src/globals.css`:
  - `.tool-block--approval`: amber left-border, ember border color
  - `.tool-block--approval-resolved`: opacity 0.6, subtle borders
  - `.approval-category-badge`: uppercase mono badge
  - `.approval-countdown`: amber Clock icon + seconds
  - `.approval-command` / `.approval-cwd`: mono command display
  - `.approval-actions`: flex row with gap
  - `.approval-btn--allow` / `--always`: green text + border
  - `.approval-btn--deny`: red text + border
  - `.approval-status--*`: color-coded resolved status text

**Architecture:**
- `approvalsRef` (Map, ref) = data store for ALL approvals (auto + user) — no re-renders
- `pendingApprovals` (Map, state) = reactive store for user-facing cards only — triggers re-renders
- Both stores updated in parallel; `approvalsRef` is authoritative, `pendingApprovals` is for UI
- Approval cards rendered after the messages list inside the scrollable `ghost-messages` div
- 120s countdown via `setInterval(1000)` in ToolApprovalCard's `useEffect`, cleaned up on unmount or lock
- After decision: card shows "Resolving…" (amber), then server ack updates to "Allowed" (green) or "Denied" (red)
- After expiry: card grays out, shows "Expired" (red)

**Tests:** 155/155 pass. Zero new TS errors. Vite build succeeds.

